    "biography": "<p>The Manscorpion Cleric, a sinister fusion of human and giant scorpion, stalks caverns, deserts, and mountains, its upper body humanoid yet its lower half a venomous arachnid menace. Wielding dark clerical powers of 8th level, these rare spellcasters rule their kind from lairs, their hatred fueling raids on human desert settlements.</p><p>Armed with a massive pole arm (dealing [[/r 3d6 #Pole arm damage]]) or other weapons, it strikes alongside a lethal tail sting ([[/r 1d10 #Tail damage]] + poison, save vs. poison or die, paralysis for [[/r 1d8-1 #Rounds paralyzed]] even if saved). Immune to scorpion venom, it wields its arsenal with chaotic precision.</p><p>Warlike and intelligent, groups of [[/r 1d8 #Manscorpions wandering]] or lairs of [[/r 2d10 #Manscorpions in lair]] hoard lavish treasures, often doubled in value. Allied only with giant scorpions, they shun other races, their spellcasting prowess (HD 8, XP 2300) a terror to all.<br><strong>Terrain:</strong> Cavern, Desert, Mountain</p>",
